</div><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/Spanring/~4/p_RgG92YcmU" height="1" width="1" alt=""/>";}i:1;a:14:{s:5:"title";s:24:"Snowboard traces in Vail";s:4:"link";s:55:"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/Spanring/~3/aiW3IpVF1fA/";s:8:"comments";s:69:"http://spanring.eu/blog/2011/01/09/snowboard-traces-in-vail/#comments";s:7:"pubdate";s:31:"Mon, 10 Jan 2011 02:39:33 +0000";s:2:"dc";a:1:{s:7:"creator";s:9:"Christian";}s:8:"category";s:60:"GeotechColoradoGeonerdGPSOpenStreetMapSnowboardingVailWinter";s:4:"guid";s:26:"http://spanring.eu/?p=9396";s:11:"description";s:304:"We had a blast last week visiting friends in Denver, Colorado. For three days we went up to Vail, which is one of the best skiing regions I&#8217;ve ever been too &#8211; great slopes and awesome back country terrain! The tiny green geonerd sitting on my shoulder made me turn my GPS on while being [...]";s:7:"content";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";s:2479:"<p>We had a blast last week visiting friends in Denver, Colorado. For three days we went up to Vail, which is one of the best skiing regions I&#8217;ve ever been too &#8211; great slopes and awesome back country terrain!</p>
<p><a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/cs___/5338459902/" title="All mine by spanaut, on Flickr"><img src="http://farm6.static.flickr.com/5288/5338459902_938cdca934.jpg" width="500" height="332" alt="All mine" /></a></p>
<p>The tiny green geonerd sitting on my shoulder made me turn my GPS on while being out on the mountain. Carrying the GPS receiver in the pocket of my jacket worked surprisingly well and resulted in about 160km of neat slope and lift traces. Here they are, shown as <a href="http://spanring.eu/files/snowboarding-vail-2011.kmz">KML overlay</a> on a Google Map&#8230;</p>
<p><iframe width="500" height="350" frameborder="0" scrolling="no" marginheight="0" marginwidth="0" src="http://maps.google.com/maps?f=q&amp;source=s_q&amp;hl=en&amp;geocode=&amp;q=http://spanring.eu/files/snowboarding-vail-2011.kmz&amp;sll=42.387585,-71.132183&amp;sspn=0.070748,0.191059&amp;ie=UTF8&amp;t=h&amp;ll=39.617855,-106.376495&amp;spn=0.045885,0.085831&amp;z=13&amp;output=embed"></iframe></p>
<p>&#8230;or here, uploaded to <a href="http://www.openstreetmap.org/user/cspanring/traces/tag/Snowboarding">OpenStreetMap</a>, waiting to be mapped and tagged for <a href="http://openpistemap.org/">OpenPisteMap</a>.</p>
